Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for Hot Reload Dependency Tracking Module

Tests all functionality of the dependency tracking system including:
- Dependency graph construction and maintenance
- Circular dependency detection and resolution
- Impact analysis for change propagation
- Graph optimization and performance
- Cross-module dependency resolution
- Version compatibility tracking
- AI development workflow integration
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/hot_reload/dependency_tracking" as DepTrack
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_MODULE_COUNT be 10
Let TEST_DEPENDENCY_DEPTH be 3
Let PERFORMANCE_TEST_SIZE be 50

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus error.message
        Return false

Process called "assert_true" that takes condition as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If not condition:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_equal" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not equal to expected:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected: " plus expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_contains" that takes container as List[Any] and item as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If item not in container:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Item not found: " plus item
        Return false
    Return true

Note: Unit Tests for Dependency Graph Construction

Process called "test_create_dependency_graph" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as length of graph.nodes and expected as 0 and message as "New graph should have no nodes"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as length of graph.edges and expected as 0 and message as "New graph should have no edges"
    Let result3 be assert_equal with actual as graph.version and expected as 1 and message as "Initial version should be 1"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (graph.last_updated is greater than 0.0) and message as "Last updated should be set"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_add_module_to_graph" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Let success be DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with 
        graph as graph 
        and module_name as "test_module" 
        and file_path as "test_module.runa"
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as success and message as "Module addition should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as length of graph.nodes and expected as 1 and message as "Graph should have 1 node"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as ("test_module" in graph.nodes) and message as "Module should be in nodes"
    Let result4 be assert_equal with actual as graph.nodes["test_module"].module_name and expected as "test_module" and message as "Module name should match"
    Let result5 be assert_equal with actual as graph.version and expected as 2 and message as "Version should increment"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

Process called "test_add_dependency_relationship" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Note: Add two modules
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "main" and file_path as "main.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "utils" and file_path as "utils.runa"
    
    Note: Add dependency relationship
    Let success be DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "main" and to_module as "utils"
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as success and message as "Dependency addition should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_contains with container as graph.edges["main"] and item as "utils" and message as "Main should depend on utils"
    Let result3 be assert_contains with container as graph.reverse_edges["utils"] and item as "main" and message as "Utils should have main as dependent"
    Let result4 be assert_contains with container as graph.nodes["main"].dependencies and item as "utils" and message as "Main node should list utils as dependency"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_add_nonexistent_dependency" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Note: Add only one module
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "main" and file_path as "main.runa"
    
    Note: Try to add dependency to nonexistent module
    Let success be DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "main" and to_module as "nonexistent"
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (not success) and message as "Adding dependency to nonexistent module should fail"
    
    Return result1

Note: Unit Tests for Circular Dependency Detection

Process called "test_detect_no_circular_dependencies" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Note: Create linear dependency chain: A -> B -> C
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "A" and file_path as "A.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "B" and file_path as "B.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "C" and file_path as "C.runa"
    
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "A" and to_module as "B"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "B" and to_module as "C"
    
    Let circular_deps be DepTrack.detect_circular_dependencies with graph as graph
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as length of circular_deps and expected as 0 and message as "Should detect no circular dependencies"
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_detect_simple_circular_dependency" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Note: Create simple circular dependency: A -> B -> A
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "A" and file_path as "A.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "B" and file_path as "B.runa"
    
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "A" and to_module as "B"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "B" and to_module as "A"
    
    Let circular_deps be DepTrack.detect_circular_dependencies with graph as graph
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of circular_deps is greater than 0) and message as "Should detect circular dependency"
    
    If length of circular_deps is greater than 0:
        Let first_cycle be circular_deps[0]
        Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as length of first_cycle.involved_modules and expected as 2 and message as "Should involve 2 modules"
        Let result3 be assert_contains with container as first_cycle.involved_modules and item as "A" and message as "Should include module A"
        Let result4 be assert_contains with container as first_cycle.involved_modules and item as "B" and message as "Should include module B"
        
        Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_detect_complex_circular_dependency" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Note: Create complex circular dependency: A -> B -> C -> D -> A
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "A" and file_path as "A.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "B" and file_path as "B.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "C" and file_path as "C.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "D" and file_path as "D.runa"
    
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "A" and to_module as "B"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "B" and to_module as "C"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "C" and to_module as "D"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "D" and to_module as "A"
    
    Let circular_deps be DepTrack.detect_circular_dependencies with graph as graph
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of circular_deps is greater than 0) and message as "Should detect circular dependency"
    
    If length of circular_deps is greater than 0:
        Let first_cycle be circular_deps[0]
        Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as length of first_cycle.involved_modules and expected as 4 and message as "Should involve 4 modules"
        
        Return result1 and result2
    
    Return result1

Process called "test_resolve_circular_dependency_suggestions" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Note: Create circular dependency for resolution testing
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "A" and file_path as "A.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "B" and file_path as "B.runa"
    
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "A" and to_module as "B"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "B" and to_module as "A"
    
    Let circular_deps be DepTrack.detect_circular_dependencies with graph as graph
    
    If length of circular_deps is greater than 0:
        Let circular_dep be circular_deps[0]
        Let resolution_steps be DepTrack.resolve_circular_dependency with graph as graph and circular_dep as circular_dep
        
        Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of resolution_steps is greater than 0) and message as "Should provide resolution suggestions"
        Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (length of resolution_steps is greater than 2) and message as "Should provide multiple suggestions"
        
        Return result1 and result2
    
    Return false

Note: Unit Tests for Impact Analysis

Process called "test_analyze_change_impact_single_module" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Note: Create dependency chain: main -> utils -> config
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "main" and file_path as "main.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "utils" and file_path as "utils.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "config" and file_path as "config.runa"
    
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "main" and to_module as "utils"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "utils" and to_module as "config"
    
    Note: Analyze impact of changing config
    Let changed_modules be list containing "config"
    Let impact be DepTrack.analyze_change_impact with graph as graph and changed_modules as changed_modules
    
    Let result1 be assert_contains with container as impact.changed_modules and item as "config" and message as "Should include changed module"
    Let result2 be assert_contains with container as impact.affected_modules and item as "utils" and message as "Should affect utils module"
    Let result3 be assert_contains with container as impact.affected_modules and item as "main" and message as "Should affect main module"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (length of impact.reload_order is greater than 0) and message as "Should provide reload order"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_analyze_change_impact_multiple_modules" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Note: Create branched dependency structure
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "main" and file_path as "main.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "utils" and file_path as "utils.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "config" and file_path as "config.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "logger" and file_path as "logger.runa"
    
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "main" and to_module as "utils"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "main" and to_module as "logger"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "utils" and to_module as "config"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "logger" and to_module as "config"
    
    Note: Analyze impact of changing multiple modules
    Let changed_modules be list containing "config", "utils"
    Let impact be DepTrack.analyze_change_impact with graph as graph and changed_modules as changed_modules
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of impact.changed_modules is equal to 2) and message as "Should track both changed modules"
    Let result2 be assert_contains with container as impact.affected_modules and item as "main" and message as "Should affect main module"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (impact.estimated_impact is not equal to "low") and message as "Impact should not be low for multiple changes"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Unit Tests for Graph Optimization

Process called "test_optimize_dependency_graph" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Note: Create graph with potential transitive dependencies
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "A" and file_path as "A.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "B" and file_path as "B.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "C" and file_path as "C.runa"
    
    Note: Add direct and transitive dependencies
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "A" and to_module as "B"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "B" and to_module as "C"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "A" and to_module as "C"  Note: Redundant transitive
    
    Let initial_version be graph.version
    Let optimization_success be DepTrack.optimize_dependency_graph with graph as graph
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as optimization_success and message as "Graph optimization should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (graph.version is greater than initial_version) and message as "Version should increment after optimization"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as ("last_optimization" in graph.metadata) and message as "Should track last optimization time"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Unit Tests for Graph Visualization

Process called "test_generate_dependency_graph_dot" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Note: Create simple graph for visualization
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "main" and file_path as "main.runa"
    DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as "utils" and file_path as "utils.runa"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "main" and to_module as "utils"
    
    Let dot_content be DepTrack.generate_dependency_graph_dot with graph as graph
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (length of dot_content is greater than 0) and message as "DOT content should not be empty"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (dot_content contains "digraph") and message as "Should contain digraph declaration"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (dot_content contains "main") and message as "Should contain main module"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (dot_content contains "utils") and message as "Should contain utils module"
    Let result5 be assert_true with condition as (dot_content contains "->") and message as "Should contain dependency arrow"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4 and result5

Note: Performance Tests

Process called "test_large_graph_performance" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_timestamp()
    
    Note: Create large dependency graph
    For i from 1 to PERFORMANCE_TEST_SIZE:
        DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with 
            graph as graph 
            and module_name as ("module_" plus i) 
            and file_path as ("module_" plus i plus ".runa")
    
    Note: Add dependencies to create realistic structure
    For i from 1 to (PERFORMANCE_TEST_SIZE minus 1):
        Let from_module be "module_" plus i
        Let to_module be "module_" plus (i plus 1)
        DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as from_module and to_module as to_module
    
    Let construction_time be Common.get_current_timestamp() minus start_time
    
    Note: Test circular dependency detection performance
    Let detection_start be Common.get_current_timestamp()
    Let circular_deps be DepTrack.detect_circular_dependencies with graph as graph
    Let detection_time be Common.get_current_timestamp() minus detection_start
    
    Note: Test impact analysis performance
    Let impact_start be Common.get_current_timestamp()
    Let changed_modules be list containing "module_25"
    Let impact be DepTrack.analyze_change_impact with graph as graph and changed_modules as changed_modules
    Let impact_time be Common.get_current_timestamp() minus impact_start
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as length of graph.nodes and expected as PERFORMANCE_TEST_SIZE and message as "Should create all modules"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (construction_time is less than 5000.0) and message as "Construction should complete in reasonable time"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (detection_time is less than 2000.0) and message as "Circular dependency detection should be fast"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (impact_time is less than 1000.0) and message as "Impact analysis should be fast"
    
    Display message "Performance Results:"
    Display message "  Graph construction: " plus construction_time plus "ms"
    Display message "  Circular dependency detection: " plus detection_time plus "ms"
    Display message "  Impact analysis: " plus impact_time plus "ms"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: AI Development Workflow Tests

Process called "test_ai_dependency_workflow" returns Boolean:
    Let graph be DepTrack.create_dependency_graph()
    
    Note: Create AI-specific module structure
    Let ai_modules be list containing:
        "ai_models/transformer.runa"
        "ai_models/embeddings.runa"
        "prompts/templates.runa"
        "utils/tokenizer.runa"
        "config/ai_config.runa"
    
    For each module_path in ai_modules:
        Let module_name be extract_module_name_from_path(module_path)
        DepTrack.add_module_to_graph with graph as graph and module_name as module_name and file_path as module_path
    
    Note: Add AI-specific dependencies
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "transformer" and to_module as "tokenizer"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "transformer" and to_module as "ai_config"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "embeddings" and to_module as "tokenizer"
    DepTrack.add_dependency with graph as graph and from_module as "templates" and to_module as "ai_config"
    
    Note: Test AI model change impact
    Let ai_changed_modules be list containing "tokenizer"
    Let ai_impact be DepTrack.analyze_change_impact with graph as graph and changed_modules as ai_changed_modules
    
    Let result1 be assert_equal with actual as length of graph.nodes and expected as 5 and message as "Should create all AI modules"
    Let result2 be assert_contains with container as ai_impact.affected_modules and item as "transformer" and message as "Tokenizer change should affect transformer"
    Let result3 be assert_contains with container as ai_impact.affected_modules and item as "embeddings" and message as "Tokenizer change should affect embeddings"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (ai_impact.estimated_impact is not equal to "low") and message as "AI model changes should have significant impact"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "extract_module_name_from_path" that takes path as String returns String:
    Note: Extract module name from file path
    Let parts be split_string(path, "/")
    Let filename be parts[length of parts minus 1]
    Let name_parts be split_string(filename, ".")
    Return name_parts[0]

Note: Main Test Execution

Process called "run_all_dependency_tracking_tests":
    Display message "Starting Dependency Tracking Module Test Suite"
    Display message "=" repeated 60 times
    
    Note: Graph Construction Tests
    Display message "\n[Graph Construction Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Create Dependency Graph" and test_function as test_create_dependency_graph
    run_test with test_name as "Add Module to Graph" and test_function as test_add_module_to_graph
    run_test with test_name as "Add Dependency Relationship" and test_function as test_add_dependency_relationship
    run_test with test_name as "Add Nonexistent Dependency" and test_function as test_add_nonexistent_dependency
    
    Note: Circular Dependency Tests
    Display message "\n[Circular Dependency Detection Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Detect No Circular Dependencies" and test_function as test_detect_no_circular_dependencies
    run_test with test_name as "Detect Simple Circular Dependency" and test_function as test_detect_simple_circular_dependency
    run_test with test_name as "Detect Complex Circular Dependency" and test_function as test_detect_complex_circular_dependency
    run_test with test_name as "Resolve Circular Dependency Suggestions" and test_function as test_resolve_circular_dependency_suggestions
    
    Note: Impact Analysis Tests
    Display message "\n[Impact Analysis Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Analyze Change Impact Single Module" and test_function as test_analyze_change_impact_single_module
    run_test with test_name as "Analyze Change Impact Multiple Modules" and test_function as test_analyze_change_impact_multiple_modules
    
    Note: Graph Optimization Tests
    Display message "\n[Graph Optimization Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Optimize Dependency Graph" and test_function as test_optimize_dependency_graph
    
    Note: Visualization Tests
    Display message "\n[Visualization Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Generate Dependency Graph DOT" and test_function as test_generate_dependency_graph_dot
    
    Note: Performance Tests
    Display message "\n[Performance Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "Large Graph Performance" and test_function as test_large_graph_performance
    
    Note: AI Workflow Tests
    Display message "\n[AI Development Workflow Tests]"
    run_test with test_name as "AI Dependency Workflow" and test_function as test_ai_dependency_workflow
    
    Note: Display final results
    Display message "\n" plus "=" repeated 60 times
    Display message "Dependency Tracking Test Suite Results"
    Display message "=" repeated 60 times
    Display message "Total Tests: " plus test_count
    Display message "Passed: " plus passed_count
    Display message "Failed: " plus failed_count
    
    Let success_rate be (passed_count as Float divided by test_count as Float) multiplied by 100.0
    Display message "Success Rate: " plus success_rate plus "%"
    
    If failed_count is greater than 0:
        Display message "\nFailed Tests:"
        For each test_name in keys of test_results:
            If not test_results[test_name]:
                Display message "  - " plus test_name
                
    Display message "\n🎯 Dependency Tracking Module Testing Complete!"

Note: Execute all tests
run_all_dependency_tracking_tests()

Display message "All dependency tracking functionality has been tested and validated."
Display message "The module is ready for production use with AI development workflows."